$0(){return'<h2>Privacy Policy</h2>\n<p><em>Last updated: June 2025</em></p>\n\n<p>KidsView ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting the privacy of children and families.\nThis Privacy Policy explains how we handle information in connection with the KidsView app.</p>\n\n<h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>\n<p>KidsView is designed with privacy in mind. We do <strong>not</strong> collect, store, or transmit any personal\ninformation from children. All data (video links, profiles, settings) is stored <strong>locally on your device only</strong>.</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Video URLs:</strong> YouTube links added by parents \u2014 stored locally on device.</li>\n  <li><strong>Kid Profiles:</strong> Names and avatars \u2014 stored locally on device.</li>\n  <li><strong>App Settings:</strong> PIN, playback preferences \u2014 stored locally on device.</li>\n  <li><strong>Watch History:</strong> Viewing records per profile \u2014 stored locally on device.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>We do <strong>not</strong> collect names, email addresses, phone numbers, or any other personal information.</p>\n\n<h3>2. Children\'s Privacy (COPPA Compliance)</h3>\n<p>KidsView is designed for use by children under parental supervision. We comply with the\nChildren\'s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA):</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>No advertisements are shown on the Kids screen.</li>\n  <li>No personal data from children is collected or transmitted.</li>\n  <li>Parents have full control over all content their child can access.</li>\n  <li>Ads (if any) are shown only in the Admin Panel, which is accessible to parents only.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>3. Third-Party Services</h3>\n<p>KidsView uses the following third-party services:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>YouTube:</strong> Videos are streamed from YouTube. YouTube\'s own privacy policy and\n  terms of service apply to video content. We do not control YouTube\'s data practices.</li>\n  <li><strong>Google AdMob:</strong> Ads are shown to parents in the Admin Panel only. AdMob may\n  use device identifiers for ad targeting. No ads are shown on the Kids screen.</li>\n  <li><strong>Google Play Billing:</strong> Used for in-app subscriptions. Google\'s privacy policy\n  applies to all payment transactions.</li>\n  <li><strong>Firebase:</strong> Used for crash reporting and analytics. No personally identifiable\n  information is linked to crash reports.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>4. Data Storage & Security</h3>\n<p>All app data is stored locally on your device using SQLite. Your Admin PIN is stored using\ndevice-level secure storage (Android Keystore / iOS Keychain). We do not have access to your PIN\nor any other data stored on your device.</p>\n\n<h3>5. Data Sharing</h3>\n<p>We do not sell, trade, or share any user data with third parties, except as required by the\nthird-party services listed above (YouTube, AdMob, Google Play).</p>\n\n<h3>6. Permissions</h3>\n<p>KidsView requests the following device permissions:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Internet:</strong> Required to load YouTube videos.</li>\n  <li><strong>Device Admin:</strong> Used for kiosk lock mode (optional \u2014 improves lock reliability).</li>\n  <li><strong>Boot Completed:</strong> To re-launch the app automatically after device restart (Device Owner mode only).</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>7. Changes to This Policy</h3>\n<p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Continued use of the app after changes\nconstitutes acceptance of the updated policy.</p>\n\n<h3>8. Contact Us</h3>\n<p>If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:</p>\n<p><strong>Email:</strong> s.m.kamalhussain@gmail.com</p>\n\n<br/>\n<p><em>By using KidsView, you agree to this Privacy Policy.</em></p>\n'},
